            "body": "`abort` was always documented to be a function in the Werkzeug docs. We will definetly not pin Werkzeug to a specific version, because that will prevent users from getting bugfixes of Werkzeug if we don't release a new Flask version everytime a new Werkzeug is released. It is established practice to pin all of your application dependencies."
